The data illustrates the process of creation of dislocation quadrupoles
in FCC Al. The density of dislocations in our data is 3.8
which is the lowest published to date and is comparable to the density
of dislocations in real crystals. The data set can be found at the fol-
detailed research article is “A topologically correct method of disloca-
tions construction for atomistic modeling” (K. Yu. Khromov et al., 2019).
